# ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
# openclaw-stack — Environment Variables
# Copy this file to .env and fill in real values. Never commit .env to git.
# ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

# ─── App ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
APP_ENV=development                         # development | staging | production
APP_VERSION=0.1.0                           # bumped per release
LOG_LEVEL=INFO                              # DEBUG | INFO | WARNING | ERROR
SECRET_KEY=change-me-generate-with-openssl-rand-hex-32   # openssl rand -hex 32
ADMIN_API_KEY=change-me-strong-random-token              # protects /admin routes

# ─── Model APIs ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-...               # console.anthropic.com → API Keys
OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-...                      # platform.openai.com → API Keys
QWEN_API_KEY=sk-...                        # dashscope.aliyuncs.com → API Keys
QWEN_BASE_URL=https://dashscope.aliyuncs.com/compatible-mode/v1  # Qwen OpenAI-compat endpoint
GEMINI_API_KEY=...                         # aistudio.google.com → Get API Key (optional)
OLLAMA_BASE_URL=http://localhost:11434     # local Ollama instance; change host if remote

# ─── Telegram ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN=...                     # legacy single-bot token (keep for /webhooks/telegram)
TELEGRAM_ALERT_CHAT_ID=...                 # your personal chat ID; get from @userinfobot
TELEGRAM_WEBHOOK_SECRET=change-me-random  # any random string; validated on incoming webhooks

# Per-agent bot tokens — each agent has its own @BotFather bot.
# Create each bot via @BotFather → /newbot, then paste the token here.
# Webhooks are registered via: python scripts/register_webhooks.py --base-url https://your-domain.com
# Unset tokens are silently skipped — not all bots need to run simultaneously.
JAKE_BOT_TOKEN=...                         # Jake — RPQ fleet ops agent
DAME_BOT_TOKEN=...                         # Dame — code & marketing agent
KOBE_BOT_TOKEN=...                         # Kobe — router & tool executor
SAM_BOT_TOKEN=...                          # Sam — sales & outreach agent
KING_BOT_TOKEN=...                         # King — deep reasoning & reports

# ─── Facebook ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
FB_PAGE_ID=...                             # Facebook Page → About → Page ID
FB_PAGE_ACCESS_TOKEN=...                   # developers.facebook.com → Graph API Explorer
FB_VERIFY_TOKEN=change-me-random          # any string; must match what you set in FB webhook dashboard

# ─── Database (PostgreSQL + pgvector) ────────────────────────────────────────────
# For local Docker: host is 'localhost' (outside Docker) or 'db' (inside Docker network)
POSTGRES_PASSWORD=change-me-strong-db-password      # used by docker-compose.yml
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://postgres:postgres@localhost:5432/openclaw
DATABASE_URL_ASYNC=postgresql+asyncpg://postgres:postgres@localhost:5432/openclaw

# ─── Supabase ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Use the SERVICE ROLE key, not the anon key — needed for server-side writes
SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project-ref.supabase.co   # app.supabase.com → Settings → API
SUPABASE_KEY=eyJ...                                  # app.supabase.com → Settings → API → service_role

# ─── Redis ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
REDIS_PASSWORD=change-me-strong-redis-password  # used by docker-compose.yml
REDIS_URL=redis://localhost:6379           # local Docker; use 'redis' as host inside Docker network

# ─── Email SMTP ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
SMTP_HOST=smtp.gmail.com                   # your SMTP server (Gmail, Resend, etc.)
SMTP_PORT=587                              # 587 for STARTTLS, 465 for SSL
SMTP_USER=you@example.com                  # SMTP login username / email
SMTP_PASSWORD=your-app-password            # Gmail: use App Password, not account password
EMAIL_FROM=OpenClaw <you@example.com>      # display name + address in From header

# ─── OpenClaw Gateway ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# NEVER expose port 18789 to the public. Use Cloudflare Tunnel or Tailscale only.
OPENCLAW_GATEWAY_URL=http://127.0.0.1:18789   # internal only; n8n uses the tunnel URL instead
OPENCLAW_AUTH_TOKEN=change-me-strong-token    # n8n sends this in Authorization header

# ─── OPS-AI Bridge ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
OPSAI_API_URL=https://ops-ai-production.up.railway.app
OPSAI_API_KEY=                             # Railway → ops-ai service → Variables → BOT_API_KEY

# ─── n8n ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
N8N_BASE_URL=https://n8n-production-3eb7.up.railway.app
N8N_API_KEY=...                            # n8n → Settings → API → Create API Key
N8N_WEBHOOK_DAILY_DIGEST=                  # n8n webhook path for workflow 05-daily-digest
N8N_WEBHOOK_MANAGER_ALERTS=               # n8n webhook path for workflow 04-manager-alerts

# ─── JWT ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
JWT_SECRET=change-me-generate-with-openssl-rand-hex-32  # openssl rand -hex 32
JWT_ALGORITHM=HS256
JWT_EXPIRE_MINUTES=1440                    # 24 hours; reduce for higher security

# ─── Cost Limits ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
DEFAULT_DAILY_BUDGET_USD=5.00              # per-agent daily spend ceiling
GLOBAL_DAILY_BUDGET_USD=50.00             # total daily ceiling across all agents
